subject: p18487334
Findings: The lungs are clear without consolidation, effusion, or pneumothorax. Left chest wall dual lead pacing device is seen with lead tips in the right atrium and right ventricular apex. Median sternotomy wires and mediastinal clips are again noted. Multiple bilateral rib fractures are noted, most of which appear chronic. There is non visualization of the cortical margin of the right posterior eighth rib fracture which raises possibility of acuity.
Impression: Multiple rib fractures identified bilaterally with possible acuity of the right posterior eighth rib fracture, to be correlated with patients site of pain. Otherwise no acute cardiopulmonary process.
